 About Virtusa
 



























UPDATE: We are reverting to the use of Virtusa to represent a single, consistent brand of Virtusa Corporation, including those of its wholly and partly owned subsidiaries. On March 3, 2016, Virtusa acquired a majority interest in Polaris Consulting & Services Limited (“Polaris”) to leverage the market presence and deep relationship that Polaris already built in the financial services space. During the integration period, we created a new market facing brand, VirtusaPolaris to represent the combined strengths of Virtusa and Polaris, including our strong software engineering heritage, deep domain expertise and focus on applying innovation to solving critical core business issues for clients. Having successfully completed the integration, we are now moving to the parent brand of Virtusa.
Virtusa is a leading worldwide provider of information technology (IT) consulting and outsourcing services. We help accelerate business outcomes for Global 2000 businesses in banking and financial services, insurance, healthcare, telecommunications and media.
Virtusa delivers targeted business outcomes through differentiated solutions by leveraging its proven platforming methodology, domain expertise and technology innovation. Virtusa’s operational excellence solutions allow businesses to improve business and operating efficiencies, and reduce costs using automation, effort compression and simplification. Virtusa’s digital transformation and innovation solutions empower companies to accelerate business growth by reimagining the consumer experience, and creating lasting value.
Virtusa is headquartered in Massachusetts and has 50 offices across North America, Europe and Asia.












About Polaris Consulting & Services Ltd. (www.polarisft.com)
Polaris Consulting & Services Ltd (BSE: POLARIS), a majority-owned subsidiary of Virtusa Corporation, is a leader in solutions and services that enable operational productivity for the global banking and financial services industry.







Executive Officers 











Kris Canekeratne

Chairman and Chief Executive Officer









Kris Canekeratne
Chairman and Chief Executive Officer
Kris A. Canekeratne, one of our co-founders, has served as chairman of our board of directors from our inception and chief executive officer from 1996 to 1997 and from 2000 to the present. As Chief Executive Officer, he plays a key role in defining the company strategy and using technology and innovation continuously to maintain its leadership in the industry. In 1997, Kris Canekeratne co-founded eDocs, Inc., a provider of electronic account management and customer care, later acquired by Oracle Corporation. In 1989, Kris Canekeratne was one of the founding team members of INSCI Corporation, a supplier of digital document repositories and integrated output management products and services and served as its senior vice president from 1992 to 1996. Canekeratne obtained his B.S. in Computer Science from Syracuse University.












Raj Rajgopal

President, Enterprise Technology & Solutions









Raj Rajgopal
President, Enterprise Technology & Solutions
Raj Rajgopal is President of Virtusa Corporation where he is responsible for developing and executing Virtusa’s growth strategy for the Enterprise Technology & Solutions group worldwide. The Enterprise Technology & Solutions group comprises Healthcare, Insurance and Lifesciences, Communications, Media, Information and Entertainment & Diversified industries.
Raj Rajgopal joined Virtusa Corporation in April 2005 and has served as the President of Virtusa Corporation since 2013. Raj served as Executive Vice President for business development and client services between 2008 and 2013, and as General Manager of the Communications, Content & Technology business unit between 2005 and 2008.
From September 1990 to April 2003, Raj held several leadership positions at Gemini Consulting, a division of Cap Gemini, both in Europe as well as in the US where he served as a Vice President of their Management Consulting Business in Media and Communications. Raj left Cap Gemini in the spring of 2003 to start his own company, Rajgopal Management Consulting, which he ran successfully for several years. As President of Rajgopal Management Consulting, Raj provided consulting services to many clients, including Virtusa.
Raj graduated from the Indian Institute of Technology with a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering; earned his M.S. in Industrial Engineering and Operations Research, and in Computer Science from Virginia Tech; and earned his Master's in Business Administration from Massachusetts Institute of Technology (M.I.T.), Sloan School of Management.












Samir Dhir

President, Banking and Financial Services 









Samir Dhir
President, Banking and Financial Services
Samir Dhir is President of Virtusa Corporation where he is responsible for developing and executing Virtusa’s growth strategy for the Banking & Financial Services industry worldwide. He is also a Board member of Virtusa Consulting Services.
Prior to being promoted to President, Banking and Financial Services, Samir led the global delivery organization at the Company as its Chief Delivery Officer. Samir is a key member of NASSCOM's IT Services Council which has been initiated to sustain and grow global leadership in IT. Samir previously worked for Wipro Technologies where he managed delivery with over 5,000 people for technology, media, transportation and services business, handled their SAP Practice and ran the managed services business. Prior to Wipro he held leadership positions with Avaya and Lucent Technologies in the UK.
Samir received his MBA from the Warwick Business School, UK and holds a B Tech from the Indian Institute of Technology Roorkee.














Ranjan Kalia

Chief Financial Officer









Ranjan Kalia
Chief Financial Officer
Ranjan Kalia has served as our executive vice president, chief financial officer, treasurer and secretary since October 2008 and prior to his promotion, served as our senior vice president, finance when he joined us in April 2008. Prior to joining us, from 2000 to December 2007, Kalia served as Vice President, Finance Emerging Markets and International Development and Chief Financial Officer-Asia Pacific for EMC Corporation. Kalia received a Masters in Business Administration from Nichols College and an undergraduate degree from Delhi University, India.












Roger Keith Modder

Chief Operating Officer









Roger Keith Modder
Chief Operating Officer
Roger Keith Modder has been with Virtusa Corporation since 2001. Prior to his promotion as Chief Operating Officer, he served as President of Asian Operations and EVP Global Services. Prior to joining Virtusa Corporation, he worked for the John Keells Group where he simultaneously held the Managing Director/Chief Executive positions for an IT systems integrator and office automation company and has over 25 years of experience in the IT industry. He is also a government nominated member of the board of directors of Nanco, (a public-private partnership for nano technology initiatives in Sri Lanka) and a member of the National Council for Economic Development (IT/BPO cluster) in Sri Lanka.












Thomas R. Holler

Chief Strategy Officer









Thomas R. Holler
Chief Strategy Officer
Thomas R. Holler has played a pivotal role in Virtusa Corporation’s journey. Prior to his promotion, he served various positions at Virtusa - Executive Vice President (Finance), Chief Financial Officer, Treasurer and Secretary since 2001. Before joining us, Holler was Chief Financial Officer and Vice President of Finance at Cerulean Technology Inc., a global supplier of wireless mobile applications and services which was later acquired by Aether Systems. Holler earned his B.S. in Business Administration from Wayne State University and his Masters in Business Administration from Northeastern University.















Sundararajan Narayanan

Chief People Officer








Sundararajan Narayanan
Chief People Officer
Sundararajan (Sundar) Narayanan is Chief People Officer at Virtusa Corporation. In this role, he oversees talent acquisition, talent management, leadership development and global immigration. His focus is on building a digital ready people organization, rich in diversity and reflecting the strong cultural values of the organization. One of his core focus areas is to also create a strong internal ecosystem that can support the leadership needs of the organization.
Sundar has over 19 years of experience in human resources and related disciplines within the information technology industry. He has held senior leadership positions in global companies, spanning compensation & benefits, training, leadership development, employee relationship management, recruitment and business HR facilitation.
Sundar has successfully designed and implemented several change management and organization development related systems and processes. He has extensive experience in integrating and streamlining various people related practices and processes in performance management, career development and training. He is hands-on and data driven in his approach and builds on his learnings having worked in various countries.
Sundar holds a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science with global certifications in HR.











Leadership Team 











Jim Francis

Senior Officer, Global Head of Healthcare, Insurance & Life Sciences









Jim Francis
Senior Officer, Global Head of Healthcare, Insurance & Life Sciences
Jim Francis is a Senior Officer and heads Virtusa Corporation’s Healthcare, Insurance & Life Sciences Business Units globally. Jim's primary focus is on client relationships, strategy and overall business growth across the above industry segments
Since joining Virtusa Corporation in 2006, Jim has held various key executive roles. These roles include Business Unit (BU) head for various industry segments such as Banking and Financial Services (BFS), Insurance, Healthcare and Diversified. Jim has also held the position of worldwide Sales head and led Virtusa’s initial expansion into Continental Europe.
Prior to joining Virtusa, Jim spent 18 years at American Management Systems (AMS), a $1 billion global IT consulting company. As Vice President and Business Unit Head within AMS's Financial Services Group his responsibilities included strategy, product management, application development and outsourcing.













Rama Sivaraman

Global Head of Independent Validation Services & Chief Operating Officer, Polaris Consulting & Services, Ltd.








Rama Sivaraman
Global Head of Independent Validation Services & Chief Operating Officer, Polaris Consulting & Services, Ltd.
Rama is the Chief Operating Officer and a board member of Polaris Consulting & Services, Ltd. She is also the Global Head of Independent Validation Services at Virtusa Corporation. In this role, she is responsible for driving growth in testing business by focusing on higher ROI for customers through innovations based on an intelligent combination of domain and technology. She is also leading the integration of Virtusa and Polaris from the Polaris side.
Prior to this, she was the Chief Operating Officer of Polaris Consulting and Services Limited, focusing on driving operational efficiency through building a 'High Performance Workplace'. With over 16 years of experience across Citigroup, Orbitech, and Polaris, Rama has held several influential roles in delivery assurance, quality control, consulting, people and culture, performance excellence and operations. A key member of the Polaris leadership team, she has spearheaded several key initiatives including, the Orbitech-Polaris merger in 2002, building a product business within Polaris (2005-2010), the restructuring of Polaris services business in 2013, and the subsequent demerger of Polaris and Intellect Design Arena Limited in 2014.
Rama has been trained as an examiner for the Ramakrishna Bajaj National Quality Award (similar to MBNQA) Model. She has presented several papers at the prestigious Global SEPG conferences organized by the Software Engineering Institute, Carnegie Mellon University. She was also a convener of WG10 ISO India Mirror Committee (IMC) and represented India at the International Meetings. She was co-editor of 15508-4 - the process assessment model for IT service management.
Rama holds a B.E. in Electronics and an MBA, both from Anna University. Rama personally drives gender diversity initiatives at the workplace and has been actively supporting the cause of increasing the representation of women in leadership positions. She is a founding member of eWIT (Empowering Women in IT) forum where she served as Vice President and President for four years and is currently an advisor and an inspiring speaker.













